on\" class=\"preview_container\" id=\"preview_18\" style=\"display: none;\"></div></span></li>\n<li><span class=\"instructure_file_holder link_holder instructure_file_link_holder\"><a class=\"file_preview_link previewable\" title=\"Akenhurst.pdf\" href=\"https://canvas.colorado.edu/courses/124722/files/80031151/download?wrap=1\" data-api-endpoint=\"https://canvas.colorado.edu/api/v1/courses/124722/files/80031151\" data-api-returntype=\"File\" aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-controls=\"preview_19\">Akenhurst “Is International Law Really Law?”</a><a class=\"file_download_btn\" role=\"button\" download=\"\" style=\"margin-inline-start: 5px; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"https://canvas.colorado.edu/courses/124722/files/80031151/download?download_frd=1\"><span role=\"presentation\"><svg viewBox=\"0 0 1920 1920\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" style=\"width:1em; height:1em; vertical-align:middle; fill:currentColor\">\n    <path d=\"m1807.093 1482.477 79.736 79.963-355.313 355.312H355.346L.035 1562.44l79.85-79.963 322.22 322.334H1484.76l322.334-322.334ZM997.677-.033v1167.02l355.313-355.313 79.962 79.85-491.858 491.633L449.46 891.524l79.962-79.85 355.313 355.313V-.033h112.941Z\" fill-rule=\"evenodd\"></path>\n</svg>\n</span><span class=\"screenreader-only\">Download Akenhurst “Is International Law Really Law?”</span></a><div role=\"region\" class=\"preview_container\" id=\"preview_19\" style=\"display: none;\"></div></span></li>\n<li><span class=\"instructure_file_holder link_holder instructure_file_link_holder\"><a class=\"file_preview_link previewable\" title=\"RussettOnealDavisTheThirdLeg.pdf\" href=\"https://canvas.colorado.edu/courses/124722/files/80031152/download?wrap=1\" data-api-endpoint=\"https://canvas.colorado.edu/api/v1/courses/124722/files/80031152\" data-api-returntype=\"File\" aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-controls=\"preview_20\">Russett, Oneal &amp; Davis “The Third Leg of the Kantian Tripod”</a><a class=\"file_download_btn\" role=\"button\" download=\"\" style=\"margin-inline-start: 5px; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"https://canvas.colorado.edu/courses/124722/files/80031152/download?download_frd=1\"><span role=\"presentation\"><svg viewBox=\"0 0 1920 1920\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" style=\"width:1em; height:1em; vertical-align:middle; fill:currentColor\">\n    <path d=\"m1807.093 1482.477 79.736 79.963-355.313 355.312H355.346L.035 1562.44l79.85-79.963 322.22 322.334H1484.76l322.334-322.334ZM997.677-.033v1167.02l355.313-355.313 79.962 79.85-491.858 491.633L449.46 891.524l79.962-79.85 355.313 355.313V-.033h112.941Z\" fill-rule=\"evenodd\"></path>\n</svg>\n</span><span class=\"screenreader-only\">Download Russett, Oneal &amp; Davis “The Third Leg of the Kantian Tripod”</span></a><div role=\"region\" class=\"preview_container\" id=\"preview_20\" style=\"display: none;\"></div></span> esp. pp. 441-449, 462</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n  \n  \n<div id=\"assign-to-mount-point\"></div>\n<div id=\"choose-editor-mount-point\"></div>",
	"contentText": "Assigned Readings and Schedule\n  \n  \n  \n    Note: the due dates for the below assigned readings will be announced as we move through the semester.\nI.A Introduction: 8/25-9/8\n\n\n\nMingst: skim Chapters 1, 2, 4, and 5. The expectation for this lengthy reading assignment is to simply become familiar with the topics.\nDiscuss with the TA: Ra’anan “The Nation-State Fallacy”\n    \n\nDownload Ra’anan “The Nation-State Fallacy”\nDiscuss with the TA: Barber “Jihad vs. McWorld”\n    \n\nDownload Barber “Jihad vs. McWorld”\n\n\n\nII.A. Realism: start on 9/10\n\n\n\n\n\nMingst pp. 67-80\nHobbes “The State of Nature …”\n    \n\nDownload Hobbes “The State of Nature …”\nThucydides “The Melian Dialogue”\n    \n\nDownload Thucydides “The Melian Dialogue”\n\n\n\n\n\nII.A. Neo-Realism: start on 9/17\n\n\n\nMingst pp. 110-114\nWaltz “The Origins of War in Neorealist Theory”\n    \n\nDownload Waltz “The Origins of War in Neorealist Theory”\n\n\n\nII.B. (Neo)Liberalism: start on 9/22\n\n\n\nMingst pp. 81-86, 116-118\nPease “Philosophical Roots of Liberalism”\n    \n\nDownload Pease “Philosophical Roots of Liberalism”\nMoravcsik “Taking Preferences Seriously”\n    \n\nDownload Moravcsik “Taking Preferences Seriously”\n\n\n\nII.C. Marxism: start on 10/1\n\n\n\nMingst: pp. 92-96\nPease “Marxism”\n    \n\nDownload Pease “Marxism”\n\n\n\nIII.A. Security: start on 10/15\n\n\n\nMingst Chapter 6\nMorgan “Deterrence: A Conceptual Analysis”\n    \n\nDownload Morgan “Deterrence: A Conceptual Analysis”\nZiegler “Disarmament”\n    \n\nDownload Ziegler “Disarmament”\nDiscuss with the TA: Ziegler “Collective Security”\n    \n\nDownload Ziegler “Collective Security”\nRussett “The Fact of the Democratic Peace”\n    \n\nDownload Russett “The Fact of the Democratic Peace”\n\n\n\nIII.B. International Economic Relations: start on 11/3\n\n\n\nMingst Chapter 8\nFrieden and Lake “International Political Economy”\n    \n\nDownload Frieden and Lake “International Political Economy”\nCoughlin et al. “Protectionist Trade Policies …”\n    \n\nDownload Coughlin et al. “Protectionist Trade Policies …”\nLenin “Imperialism: The Highest Stage of Capitalism”\n    \n\nDownload Lenin “Imperialism: The Highest Stage of Capitalism”\nCohn “Dependency Theory”\n    \n\nDownload Cohn “Dependency Theory”\nRussett & Oneal “Triangulating Peace”\n    \n\nDownload Russett & Oneal “Triangulating Peace” esp. pp. 127-133, 154-155\n\n\n\nIII.C. International Institutions and Law: start on 11/17\n\n\n\nMingst Chapters 9 and 7\nPease “Liberalism and the Nature of International Organizations”\n    \n\nDownload Pease “Liberalism and the Nature of International Organizations”\nAkenhurst “Is International Law Really Law?”\n    \n\nDownload Akenhurst “Is International Law Really Law?”\nRussett, Oneal & Davis “The Third Leg of the Kantian Tripod”\n    \n\nDownload Russett, Oneal & Davis “The Third Leg of the Kantian Tripod” esp. pp. 441-449, 462\n\n\n\n \n  \n  \n\n",
